Propmt A
Here's your personalized 30-day Data Science roadmap, built for a complete beginner with 1–2 hours a day.

**How to use it:** Click through the four weekly tabs, mark each day done as you complete it, and watch your progress bar fill up. Your progress is saved automatically.

**The four-week arc:**

- **Week 1** gets Python installed and running — no prior coding needed. You'll be writing real scripts by day 7.
- **Week 2** introduces Pandas, the workhorse of data science. You'll learn to load, clean, and query datasets.
- **Week 3** is about turning numbers into pictures — charts, heatmaps, and a full exploratory analysis notebook.
- **Week 4** is where it gets exciting: training your first machine learning models to make predictions.

**Each week ends with a real project** you can put on a GitHub portfolio — the Titanic ML project in Week 4 is an actual Kaggle competition you can submit.

All resources listed are free. A good sequence to follow: Kaggle's mini-courses (fastest, hands-on) → YouTube when you need a concept explained visually → official docs as your reference.

By day 30, you'll have Python, Pandas, Matplotlib, and scikit-learn under your belt — exactly the stack entry-level data roles expect to see.

















PROMPT B
📅 WEEK 1: Python for Data Science + Math Foundations
🎯 Milestone: Master Python libraries (NumPy, Pandas) + Refresh Statistics basics

Daily Tasks:
Day	Topic	Tasks (3-4 hrs)
Day 1	Python Refresher for DS	Review Python (lists, dicts, functions, OOP basics). Setup: Anaconda + Jupyter Notebook + VS Code
Day 2	NumPy Basics	Arrays, indexing, slicing, broadcasting, math operations. Solve 10 NumPy exercises
Day 3	NumPy Advanced	Reshaping, aggregation, random module. Mini task: Build a matrix calculator
Day 4	Pandas Basics	Series, DataFrames, reading CSV/Excel, indexing. Practice on Titanic dataset
Day 5	Pandas Advanced	GroupBy, merge, join, pivot tables, handling missing data
Day 6	Statistics Crash Course	Mean, median, mode, variance, std dev, distributions (normal, binomial), probability basics
Day 7	🏆 Mini Project + Review	Project 1: Exploratory Data Analysis on Titanic Dataset (Kaggle). Post on GitHub!
📚 Resources for Week 1:
🎥 Video: Python for Data Science – freeCodeCamp (12 hrs)
📖 Read: "Python Data Science Handbook" by Jake VanderPlas (free online)
📝 Practice: Kaggle Learn – Python & Pandas Courses
📊 Stats: Khan Academy – Statistics & Probability
📅 WEEK 2: Data Visualization + SQL + Advanced Statistics
🎯 Milestone: Tell stories with data + Master SQL (crucial for interviews!)

Day	Topic	Tasks (3-4 hrs)
Day 8	Matplotlib	Line, bar, scatter, histogram plots. Customize charts
Day 9	Seaborn	Heatmaps, pairplots, distribution plots, box plots
Day 10	SQL Basics	SELECT, WHERE, ORDER BY, GROUP BY, HAVING. Practice on SQLBolt
Day 11	SQL Intermediate	JOINS (INNER, LEFT, RIGHT), Subqueries, Aggregations
Day 12	SQL Advanced	Window functions, CTEs, ranking. Solve 15 SQL problems on HackerRank/LeetCode
Day 13	Inferential Statistics	Hypothesis testing, p-value, t-test, chi-square, correlation vs causation
Day 14	🏆 Project + Review	Project 2: Sales Data Analysis Dashboard (using Pandas + Seaborn). Write a blog/LinkedIn post!
📚 Resources for Week 2:
🎥 Video: Matplotlib & Seaborn Tutorial – Corey Schafer
📝 SQL Practice: SQLBolt, HackerRank SQL, LeetCode SQL 50
📖 Read: "Storytelling with Data" by Cole Nussbaumer (selected chapters)
📅 WEEK 3: Machine Learning Fundamentals
🎯 Milestone: Build & evaluate your first ML models

Day	Topic	Tasks (3-4 hrs)
Day 15	ML Intro + Scikit-learn	Types of ML (supervised/unsupervised). Train-test split, basic workflow
Day 16	Linear Regression	Theory + implementation. Evaluate with R², MAE, RMSE
Day 17	Logistic Regression	Classification basics. Confusion matrix, precision, recall, F1-score
Day 18	Decision Trees + Random Forest	How they work, build models, feature importance
Day 19	KNN + Naive Bayes	Algorithm intuition + implementation
Day 20	Unsupervised Learning	K-Means Clustering, PCA basics
Day 21	🏆 Project + Review	Project 3: House Price Prediction (Regression) OR Loan Approval Classifier. Push to GitHub with README
📚 Resources for Week 3:
🎥 Video: Machine Learning with Python – freeCodeCamp
📖 Book: "Hands-On ML with Scikit-Learn" by Aurélien Géron (Ch 1-4)
📝 Practice: Kaggle Learn – Intro to ML + Intermediate ML
📅 WEEK 4: Interview Prep + Capstone Project + Resume
🎯 Milestone: Be 100% interview-ready with portfolio + confidence

Day	Topic	Tasks (3-4 hrs)
